<div id="pf2e06" class="pf w49 h233" data-page-no="2e06"><div class="pc pc2e06 w49 h233"><div class="t m62a x0 h32 y2aee ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III. Other Ways of Witnessing </div><div class="t m41c x11 he y2a2b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. </div><div class="t me0d x73 he y2a2b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Considering others. Phil. 2:4; 1 Cor. </div><div class="t m8d2 x48 he y2b1c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10:24. </div><div class="t m41c x11 he y2a6f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. </div><div class="t m776 x48 he y2a6f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Dealing with troublemakers. </div><div class="t m1355 x73 he y2a9c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Cor. 2:5-8. </div><div class="t m41c x56 he y2984 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t m244 x9f he y29c8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bearing others&apos; burdens. Gal. 6:1, </div><div class="t m193b x9 he y2b07 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 ; Rom. 15:1-3. </div><div class="t m41c x56 he y29d8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. </div><div class="t m176 x9f he y2ae7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Unselfishness rewarded. 1 Kings </div><div class="t mcdb x9f he y2a1d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3:9-12; 4:29. </div><div class="t m25c x97 h32 y20ea ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE LESSON </div><div class="t meaa x6e he yd36 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NorE.—Goodspeed renders this verse, </div><div class="t m291 x90 he y1480 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;You must always treat other people as </div><div class="t m69a x90 he y1135 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">you would like to have them treat you, </div><div class="t me9 x45 he yca7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for this sums up the Law and the Proph-</div><div class="t m149f x90 he y1fca ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ets.&quot;—The </div><div class="t m33b x4c h21 y1f0c ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">New Testament, an American </div><div class="t m1177 x45 h21 yd52 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Translation, </div><div class="t m165c x76 he y15cd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by Edgar J. Goodspeed, copy-</div><div class="t m3a3 x45 he y979 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">right 1923 by the University of Chicago </div><div class="t ma0a x90 he y1fd5 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Press. Used by permission. </div><div class="t m1113 xbc he y10c1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. How would Job have treated his </div><div class="t mdfd x90 he y12ba ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">self-righteous friends if they had been </div><div class="t m97d x45 he y1c2e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in his place? Job 16:2-5. </div><div class="t m708 x83 h32 y96d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Introduction </div><div class="t m3bc xe he y1510 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The standard of the golden rule is the </div><div class="t m72b x0 he ye93 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">true standard of Christianity; anything </div><div class="t m16d x0 he y1081 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">short of it is a deception. A religion that </div><div class="t m5a3 x0 he y1cd0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">leads men to place a low estimate upon </div><div class="t mddc x0 he y7ca ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">human beings, whom Christ has esteemed </div><div class="t m6e5 x0 he y13ad ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of such value as to give Himself for them; </div><div class="t m9f5 x0 he y1f12 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">a religion that would lead us to be care-</div><div class="t mb3b x0 he yff2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">less of human needs, sufferings, or rights, is </div><div class="t m5b9 x0 he y119f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">a spurious religion. . . . </div><div class="t m16b xe he y1439 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Search heaven and earth, and there is </div><div class="t m722 x0 he y11de ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">no truth revealed more powerful than that </div><div class="t m14db x0 he y10ce ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which is made manifest in works of mercy </div><div class="t m764 x0 he y1c8f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to those who need our sympathy and aid. </div><div class="t m7ae x0 he yf29 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This is the truth as it is in Jesus. When </div><div class="t md0e x0 he y11a6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">those who profess the name of Christ shall </div><div class="t mc4 x0 he y129f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">practice the principles of the golden rule, </div><div class="t m259 x0 he y1387 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the same power will attend the gospel as in </div><div class="t m15b0 x0 he y143c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">apostolic </div><div class="t m45a x60 h21 y1cc7 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">times.&quot;—Thoughts From the </div><div class="t m42f x0 h21 y108b ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mount of Blessing, </div><div class="t m64b xf he y104f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pages 136, 137. </div><div class="t m908 xe h32 yfe2 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Humanity Needs Understanding </div><div class="t m1048 x15 he y13c0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m728 x4a he y11c6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What evasive question did Cain </div><div class="t m697 x0 he yecc ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ask of the Lord? Gen. 4:9. </div><div class="t me8 xe he y1103 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NarE.—&quot;There has been too much of a </div><div class="t m695 x0 he y1104 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spirit to ask, &apos;Am I my brother&apos;s keeper?&apos; </div><div class="t m624 x0 he y1057 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Said the angel: &apos;Yea, </div><div class="t m7f3 x2c h21 y1057 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">thou </div><div class="t m109 x5e he y1dac ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">art thy brother&apos;s </div><div class="t m85c x0 he y1441 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">keeper. Thou shouldest have a watchful </div><div class="t m32e x0 he y1fd3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">care for thy brother, be interested for his </div><div class="t m238 x0 he y1110 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">welfare, and cherish a kind, loving spirit </div><div class="t m6c x0 he y1149 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">toward him. Press together, press together.&apos; </div><div class="t m200 x0 he y1461 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God designed that man should be open-</div><div class="t m6b9 x0 he y2047 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">hearted and honest, without affectation, </div><div class="t m73d x0 he y1239 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">meek, humble, with simplicity. This is the </div><div class="t mda9 x0 he y1dc7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">principle of heaven; God ordered it so. But </div><div class="t m5fd x0 he y1fb5 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">poor, frail man has sought out something </div><div class="t me0d x0 he yfd6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">different—to follow his own way, and care-</div><div class="t m9d3 x0 he y1122 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fully attend to his own self-interest.&quot;—</div><div class="t mcbc x0 h21 y114f ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Testimonies, vol. </div><div class="t m733 x7e he y1522 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1, pp. 113, 114. </div><div class="t m1f3 x15 he y11c8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m620 x4a he yde7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What divine rule has been given </div><div class="t m11a4 x0 he y1c3e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to regulate human relationships? </div><div class="t mbbc x0 he yf0d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matt. 7:12. </div><div class="t m434 x6e he y10d6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NorE.—&quot;Job&apos;s professed friends were </div><div class="t mb35 x90 he y1177 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">miserable comforters, making his case more </div><div class="t m4aa x90 he y136b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bitter and unbearable, and job was not </div><div class="t ma1b x90 he y10e0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">guilty as they </div><div class="t m1364 x57 h21 y1fbf ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">supposed.&quot;—Testimonies to </div><div class="t m1bbe x45 h21 y12f9 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ministers, </div><div class="t m7d5 xac he y1179 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">page 350. </div><div class="t mb97 xbc he y1f76 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;&apos;If I were in your place,&apos; Job declares, </div><div class="t ma6d x90 he y19d3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in effect, &apos;I would not act as you have </div><div class="t m2ce x90 he y746 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">acted. I would comfort and encourage </div><div class="t mda9 x90 he y1c68 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">you.&apos; </div><div class="t m362 x4b h21 y1c68 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;—S.D.A. Bible Commentary, </div><div class="t m9e x165 he y11ae ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">on Job </div><div class="t m1853 x90 he y1be2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16 : 5. </div><div class="t me8c xb0 he y12fb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The inhumanity of man toward man is </div><div class="t ma4 x45 he y1d3d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">our greatest sin. Many think that they are </div><div class="t m2c0 x45 he y1c6a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">representing the justice of God while they </div><div class="t m781 x90 he y74b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">wholly fail of representing His tenderness </div><div class="t m7b7 x90 he y1ec4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and His great love. Often the ones whom </div><div class="t m635 x90 he y15c1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">they meet with sternness and severity are </div><div class="t m813 x90 he y1220 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">under the stress of temptation. Satan is </div><div class="t ma3 x90 he y1d2e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">wrestling with these souls, and harsh, un-</div><div class="t m6da x90 he yead ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sympathetic words discourage them and </div><div class="t m67d x45 he y118e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cause them to fall a prey to the tempter&apos;s </div><div class="t m1143 x45 he y1ddb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">power.&quot;—The </div><div class="t maae xa6 h21 y1340 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ministry of Healing, </div><div class="t m547 x175 he yf4a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">page </div><div class="t m1f99 x90 he y1c34 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">163. </div><div class="t m3b6 xbc he y1ce8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. After David had sinned in num-</div><div class="t m6db x90 he ya1c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bering Israel, what choices did God </div><div class="t m183 x90 he y14dd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">offer him? What did he choose, and </div><div class="t m529 x90 he yeea ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">why? 2 Sam. 24:10-14. </div><div class="t m1b5 x6e he y1064 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NorE.—&quot;I am in great distress,&quot; is the </div><div class="t m1dc x45 he y146a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">R.S.V. translation of verse 14. &quot;Let us fall </div><div class="t m428 x90 he y11cb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">into the hand of the Lord, for His mercy </div><div class="t m154d x3c h34 y11cc ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[27</div><div class="t m2571 x90 h2f y11cc ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">] </div><div class="t m3f8 x1f h2f y11cc ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
